  "texts": [
    "A Case description and Gemini analysis of the case; B when asked for surgical advice, Google Gemini provided more synthetic answers rich of web sources; C when asked to choose only one treatment, Gemini frequently answered \"I can't choose one treatment for this case.\"",
    "However, it was able to present a list of surgical options, even though none of them was analyzed in details discussed the case, and if a univocal choice could not be reached, the case was excluded from the study.",
    "Since it was impossible to obtain a comprehensive scenario outline, six patients with incomplete medical histories or anamnesis, missing preoperative data or surgical records on the computer system, or receiving surgery straight from the emergency department were excluded from the study.",
    "In fact, the lack of complete pre-operative data raised doubts between the specialists and determined inconsistent results derived from chatbots' answers.A correct agreement between chatbots and specialists was considered real only if the chosen treatment of both were the same.",
    "If the chatbot was not able to pick one treatment among the presented list, but the answer was indeed present in the list, we defined it as \"partial agreement.\""
  ],
